# Open a markdown file that exercises:
#  - heading (`text.title` capture)
#  - inline emphasis (`**bold**` — markdown_inline injection)
#  - fenced rust code block (rust injection through markdown's
#    `injection.language` capture)
#
# All three drive highlight spans through different injection paths;
# a regression in any of them shows up as fewer total spans.
write notes.md # Title\n\nThis is **bold** and *em* text.\n\n```rust\nfn main() { let x = 1; }\n```\n
open notes.md
# 2026-07 [ui] `.md` files route to MdPreview by default. Swap
# to the raw editor so tree-sitter highlighting fires (preview
# panes have no `highlights` field to count).
command markdown.edit_raw
expect pane "notes.md"
expect screen contains "Title"
expect screen contains "**bold**"
expect screen contains "fn main()"
# Heading + 2 emphasis runs + fenced code spans + rust grammar
# inside the fence. ≥ 6 is conservative.
expect highlights at_least 6
